rComments: I enjoy taking the class with the prof. I would like to take the other class with her in the future. Her lecture is a bit boring, but assignments and group projects are not hard to do as long as you put the effort in. I am very proud of my groupmates. Highly recommended this class, the course load is not too bad.

Professor Jaya is an awesome prof. She has a great personality and is always willing to help. The course itself is a group-based, which means you have to work with other people. I was so lucky to have such a group that everyone contributed a lot to this course and ended A+s for all group projects we did.

This class was quite laid back during online teaching. Everything was pretty straightforward, there were a few group projects and open book exam and midterm. The course matter wasn't super interesting but she did her best to make it interesting and relatable to the real world.

She is pretentious and thinks she is the smartess person in the room. She will blatantly insult you with no remorse and will never apologize for her wrongdoing. She will not answer to you if you don't address her as '' dr ''. Just a rude and pretentious teacher, will never take her again!

The class was fairly easy but the prof was not. She was weirdly intense sometimes and would constantly force you to speak. The class got boring after the first two or three sessions. She liked to talk over you and got a strong attitude if you didn't play along. Be prepared to be scolded if you got on her nerves. Overall generic class though.

Prof. Jaya was an easy prof, however super boring material. There was about 6 in-class assignments which was worth 20%. They were easy but you have to come. Easy group project/presentation. I hate group work, but this class was bearable.
Not an interesting course matter to begin with, but she really isn't great at teaching it. She doesn't like when students don't participate in class.

Professor Jaya is an excellent prof! She explains course content in a way that is clear to understand and provides good feedback on assignments. She is also always willing to answer questions to help students have a better understanding of what is being taught in the course. I strongly recommend taking classes with Professor Jaya!
She is one of the best profs in communications for sure. She is super straight forward and does not let mistakes fly by, she always provides corrections in a non condescending way.
Dry lecture, lots of group work. Lots of time to do group work. Easy marks and midterm, take home final.

I didnt show up to any classes other than the group projects. Easy marks if you do and answer the questions with your group of your choice. Take home midterm and final exam which gives you an easy mark. Watch your grammar though. She cares about it. The material is basic stuff, easy to understand. Buy the text, read the slides & maybe participate.
It is a second-year course and the prof rather grades grammar and style than the content.

I didn't learn a lot from her. Her lectures basically just the summaries of the textbook. The marker is consist of group paper, group presentation, individual midterm and final take-home, and participation markers. Grading criteria are extremely unclear. And I really do not understand why she made grammar counts for half of the midterm marker.
Very nice prof! Lectures were dry but take home midterm and final.

Although her lectures were very dry, it was clear she was very knowledgeable on the subject. She used many examples from her own research to try and make the class more interesting. Participation and group projects but she marks fair.

This prof doesn't get enough credit! While the material can be dry, she is passionate! All assignments, midterms, exams etc are straight forward including the group work! Put a little bit of effort in and you're fine! I respect her efforts to get us involved! Love to have her again even if a more dry course

This is a mandatory class for students in communications. Compared with cmn3102 this course was much easier. there is a group project which is pretty easy. midterm is m/c so super easy. Theres little assignments every other week, but it is also a group thing so nothing to worry about. finals are taken home questions, which she limits to 100 words.
very condescending if you ask what she believes is a stupid question. easy tho, if you don't know how to work in a group, or use contexts to answer questions don't take this class

I absolutely loved having her as a prof. She is a very caring instructor who only wants her students to succeed. If you come to class and class discussions, actually try... you will end up with a good mark. Overall a great professor who I would recccomend to everyone. LOVED HER!!

Personally, I enjoyed having a course with her.  Group questions every week, but they're not difficult. She posts the notes online so no reason to buy the textbook. The group presentation was easy and the paper wasn't too hard either. TAKE HOME EXAM! 100 words per question and there is 6 questions. Mid - term was average, could have been less wordy
Boring lectures. PArticipation thats basically free marks. Easy enough group projects.

Very dry lectures generally with reading directly from slides. Participation classes every now and then which get quite annoying and aren't super useful but are free marks so w/e. Not a super difficult class, group project at the end which was short etc.

Had her once in 4th year. Very boring class. Exams are comprised of MC straight from slides. Study and you'll do well. Attendance is 20% which sounds easy, but you MUST participate in these terrible group activities or "skits" (like in Drama class). I sacrificed 10% of attendance by avoiding these skits. Yes, it is as lame and corny as it sounds.
Boring boring and just boring.useless, not helpful at all. Avoid!
boring, and am sure she has no background in communication :(

Dry material, but her exams are straight-forward and come right from the slides. In-class activities are long, but you will get full marks for participating. Group paper and presentation are also very straight-forward. She is very friendly and likes to get to know her students. I recommend taking this course with her.

She made a very boring class very tolerable. Her exams are straightforward short answer questions. The group assignment was tedious and boring, but she's a fair marker so it works out. Overall she's a good prof and you can tell she's passionate about research.

She is so much fun! The class would have been very boring without her assigning the class to put on skits at the end of class! The class assignments are 2 essays worth 40% each and the 20% for participation. The textbooks are useless don't buy them. Go to class, ask questions, and you'll have fun! Great Prof!

made a boring class at least somewhat fun. annoyed that she had two expensive and required textbooks and then didnt let us use them for our papers, but other thn that she is a great prof and can be a lot of fun

This professor fails to listen to students' concerns           It is extremely difficult to ask questions about assignments as she is stubborn and uncompromising                  Overall this professor was average----not extraordinary but informative

Want an easy A, but nearly die from boredom, learn nothing and be force to attend of lose 20% of yur grade? Then this is the class for you. Content feels like you're back in 2nd grade learning right and wrong. No depth, nothing even noteworthy. She spends the class reading off her purple and white slides. These people like her for the free grade.

if you don't have the attitude that the class is a joke and you can actually take it seriously, you will get an A guarunteed - big mistake of those who skipped an easy mark! the tests are so easy & she's very friendly. do not buy the newest textbook for $100, i got the old for $20 and i passed with an A!
LAYOS!

Her friendliness is overshadowed by the uselessness of the content and the enormously overrated participation mark. These factors made my overall impression of her class to be one of disgruntlement and despair.

Extremely kind and helpful. Loves to have interactions with her students and really seems to understand how many of us feel. No wonder she's teaching Interpersonal Communications! Exam not too tough, but you do need to study. Recommended for sure.
She should be the professor of choice for Interpersonal Communication. Fair marker.
